<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=449432">www.magelo.com/eq_view_pr...num=449432</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--> <br>
<br>
<br>
I am not anywhere near the MT for my guild...in fact, I am close to the lowest level warrior played as a main. We are moving to NToV etc, but the other tanks above me are 61x2, 59, 58, 56, 54 and 52. And they all need equipment before me.<br>
<br>
Hence, my position is a little different from the norm, as I have both the luxury of not needing to level up ASAP...and the downside being that the really good equipment will be out of my reach for a while yet. Which is fair enough.<br>
<br>
So my questions :<br>
1. Would it be worth ditching the Frosty, buying another decent taunting weapon as cheap as possible and getting some armour upgrades?<br>
<br>
2. I plan to level up to around 54/55...then start accruing AAXP (remember, I am not required to be tanking anything for my guild at this time....).....is this worth doing, because my stamina and dex are pretty low, and as I am not going to be in line for much in the way of equipment upgrades (although I do attend the raids that I am of a level for)...opinions??<br>
<br>
<br>
Thanks<br>
Keb<br>
