etter for awhile.  Your other inventory slots have lot's of improvement options.  Depending on how your guild works, you will probably have chances at armor being passed down, or armor that would rot because people don't need it.  The armor will come to you eventually, but I think you'd regret selling the FB.<br>
<br>
I was in a similar situation to you once, and when my guild killed Cazic for the first time, we lost all 6 of our MT's.  I was the only warrior left, and was very thankful that I had my FB.  I was actually able to get and hold aggro on CT long enough for our tanks to battle rez and finish off the fight.  I still laugh when I remember my surprise at hearing the raid leader say, &quot;Blaeric you are up!&quot;.<br>
<br>
~Blaeric<br>
